Real-Time Email Phishing Detection

This project detects phishing emails using a hybrid deep learning model
(CNN + LSTM) combined with a Q-learning agent for real-time adaptive detection.

Tech stack: Python, TensorFlow, CNN, LSTM, Reinforcement Learning.
 Real-Time Email Phishing Detection using CNN, LSTM & Q-Learning

 Project Overview
This project implements a **real-time email phishing detection system** using a hybrid
**CNN + LSTM deep learning model**, enhanced with a **Q-learning agent** for adaptive
decision-making.

The deep learning model performs phishing classification, while the reinforcement
learning agent dynamically learns optimal actions in real-time email detection scenarios.

---

 üß† Problem Statement
Traditional phishing detection systems are static and struggle to adapt to evolving
attack patterns. This project addresses the need for an **intelligent, adaptive, and
real-time phishing detection system**.

---

## üîß Tech Stack
- **Programming:** Python
- **Data Analysis:** Pandas, NumPy
- **NLP:** Tokenization, Padding, Word Embeddings
- **Deep Learning:** CNN, LSTM
- **Reinforcement Learning:** Q-Learning
- **Frameworks:** TensorFlow / Keras
- **Visualization:** Matplotlib, Seaborn
- **Tools:** Jupyter Notebook

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è System Architecture
1. Email text preprocessing and tokenization
2. Feature extraction using word embeddings
3. **CNN layers** for local textual pattern detection
4. **LSTM layer** for sequence modeling
5. Phishing probability prediction
6. **Q-learning agent** for real-time decision optimization
7. Final action: classify, flag, or allow email

---

 Role of Q-Learning Agent
- Learns optimal actions based on detection confidence
- Adapts to new phishing patterns over time
- Improves real-time response effectiveness
- Reduces false positives and false negatives dynamically

---

 üìä Results
- High phishing detection accuracy using CNN + LSTM
- Improved real-time performance with Q-learning integration
- Adaptive behavior in dynamic email environments

## üìä Model Performance

The CNN + LSTM model with Q-learning achieved strong performance on the test dataset.

| Metric     | Score |
|-----------|-------|
| Accuracy  | 98%   |
| Precision | 98%   |
| Recall    | 98%   |
| F1-Score  | 98%   |

**Confusion Matrix:**
- True Negatives: 3885
- False Positives: 115
- False Negatives: 61
- True Positives: 3939

‚úÖ High recall ensures most phishing emails are detected, while strong precision
reduces false alerts for legitimate emails.


